description._content: Digital ID: 482025. The V-8 series 65 is a new member of the Cadillac family for 1937. Notes: It is built in only this four-door body type and mounted on a 131-inch wheelbase. The car is designed for owners who demand more room than in the conventional body type. Source: Photographs of General Motors and Chrysler car and truck models, 1902 - 1938. / 1902-1938.
